Hey guys, @squidplains here to explain the joke. 

So basically, this post is assessing what would happen if a university were to burn down. It talks about the compensation the students attending the uni would receive for having to undergo such a tragic event which could potentially put them in danger and harm their mental health or permanently scar them. All students that fall victim to such a crisis receive a Bachelor's degree and get to graduate. Some may see this as something they hope never occurs but others think about using this opportunity to their advantage. On the bottom portion of the photo, we can see Phineas (from the American animated series Phineas and Ferb) saying one of his most remarkable catchphrases - "Hey Ferb, I know what we're gonna do today". In the show, he remarks these words when an idea, which he would like to pursue, sparks into his mind. Looking at the current situation of this meme, make out that the "idea wanting to be pursued" is going ahead and burning down a university, so that everyone can pass without having to tolerate all the revision and exams.
